27/04/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police chiefs from Southeast Europe wrapped up a meeting in Sarajevo on Tuesday (26 April), agreeing to improve co-operation in fighting organised crime and the exchange of information.
The forum, held as part of the Southeast Europe Police Chiefs' Association (SEPCA), was aimed at adopting a draft resolution to be voted on next month during the official SEPCA conference in Macedonia.
(Dnevni avaz - 27/04/05;
PBS BiH, NTV Hayat - 26/04/05)
